source_description: The RudderStack AMP component makes it easy to send the event data from your AMP page to numerous destinations through RudderStack. Now you don't need to implement or test multiple components for different destinations for your event data. This component collects the default properties and sends a page event to RudderStack.
destination_description:
Google Tag Manager is a popular tag management system that allows you to quickly update tags for your web or mobile applications. Once added to your project, it makes it easier for you to configure, deploy and measure your tags from a web-based UI without needing additional code.

RudderStack enables you to send events to the GTM dataLayer using the JavaScript SDK. This document explains in detail how to do that.
use_case_desc_1: Simplify instrumentation by sending existing data variables to Google Tag Manager
use_case_desc_2: Easily deploy third party scripts through a single RudderStack SDK
use_case_desc_3: Significantly improve site speed by replacing Google Tag Manager with RudderStack
relevant_integration_desc_1: Use the AMP pages to send real-time data to Google Analytics
relevant_integration_desc_2: Easily send event stream and batch data to Amazon S3 from your  AMP pages
relevant_integration_desc_3: Automatically send data from your AMP pages to any destination that supports Webhooks
relevant_integration_desc_4: Send product data from your AMP pages to Amplitude in a few clicks.

meta_desc: Don’t go through the pain of direct integration. RudderStack’s  Ruby SDK makes it easy to send data from your Ruby app to Amazon Redshift ...and all of your other cloud tools.
source_description: RudderStack’s Ruby SDK allows you to track your customer event data from your Ruby code. Once enabled, the event requests hit the RudderStack servers. RudderStack then routes the events to the specified destination platforms as configured by you.
destination_description: Amazon Redshift is the world's fastest cloud data warehouse. It allows you to handle large analytical workloads with best-in-class performance, speed, and efficiency. With Redshift, you don't have to worry about the scale of your data or the cost of running queries on them.
use_case_desc_1: Simplify your workflow with predefined schemas, automatically created for you in your Amazon Redshift warehouse.
use_case_desc_2: Leverage best in class sync times and load data to Amazon Redshift every 30 minutes (or even faster!).
use_case_desc_3: Customize data and loads for Amazon Redshift across multiple databases and schemas.
relevant_integration_desc_1: Use the Ruby app to send real-time data to Google Analytics
relevant_integration_desc_2: Easily send event stream and batch data to Amazon S3 from your  Ruby app
relevant_integration_desc_3: Automatically send data from your Ruby app to any destination that supports Webhooks
relevant_integration_desc_4: Send product data from your Ruby app to Amplitude in a few clicks.
